基因工程是改变生物的遗传组成使用的技术，包括了删除可遗传材料，和将生物体外直接制备的DNA导入[[宿主|宿主]]或[[细胞|细胞]]，然后与宿主融合或[[杂交|杂交]]。<ref name = "EU17">{{Cite journal|title=Directive on the release of genetically modified organisms (GMOs) Directive 2001/18/EC ANNEX I A|publisher=Official Journal of the European Communities|date=2001-03-12|author=The European Parliament and the council of the European Union|url=http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2001:106:0001:0038:EN:PDF|page=17|postscript=<!--None-->|journal=|access-date=2017-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723050044/http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=OJ:L:2001:106:0001:0038:EN:PDF|archive-date=2017-07-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 这涉及使用重组核酸（DNA或RNA）技术来形成可遗传材料的新组合，然后通过[[运载体|载体]]系统（基因工程载体）间接地或通过显微注射、大量注射和[[微囊化技术|微囊化技术]]直接地掺入该材料。

“基因工程”並不包括传统的动物和植物育种、[[体外受精|体外受精]]、[[染色體倍性|多倍体]]育种、[[人工诱变|人工诱变]]和[[細胞融合|细胞融合]]技术，因为在该过程中不使用经过重组核酸或遗传修饰的生物体。<ref name = "EU17"/>[[欧洲联盟|欧盟]]则将“遗传工程”广泛定义为包括[[选择育种|选择育种]]和其他人工选择手段；严格说来，遗传工程（genetic engineering）的范围较基因工程（gene engineering）广泛。<ref>Staff [http://ec.europa.eu/agriculture/publi/gmo/gmo.pdf Economic Impacts of Genetically Modified Crops on the Agri-Food Sector; P. 42 Glossary - Term and Definitions] {{Wayback|url=http://ec.europa.eu/agriculture/publi/gmo/gmo.pdf |date=20130514202621 }} The European Commission Directorate-General for Agriculture, "Genetic engineering: The manipulation of an organism's genetic endowment by introducing or eliminating specific genes through modern molecular biology techniques. A broad definition of genetic engineering also includes selective breeding and other means of artificial selection.",  Retrieved 5 November 2012</ref>[[克隆|克隆]]和[[干细胞|干细胞]]技术，虽然不被认为是基因工程，<ref>{{cite web|title=Is Livestock Cloning Another Form of Genetic Engineering?|last=VanEenennaam|first=Alison|publisher=agbiotech|url=http://agribiotech.info/details/Alison%20%20cloning%20March%208%20%2003.pdf|accessdate=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110511121055/http://agribiotech.info/details/Alison%20-%20cloning%20March%208%20-%2003.pdf|archivedate=2011-05-11}}</ref>但也是与基因工程密切相关的，可以在其中使用基因工程。<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Swiss Med Wkly|year=2006|volume=136|issue=27–28|pages=413–415|title=Genetic engineering of embryonic stem cells|first1=David M.|last1=Suter|first2=Michel|last2=Dubois-Dauphin|first3=Karl-Heinz|last3=Krause|url=http://www.smw.ch/docs/pdf200x/2006/27/smw-11406.PDF|pmid=16897894|access-date=2017-02-08|archive-date=2011-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707003215/http://www.smw.ch/docs/pdf200x/2006/27/smw-11406.PDF|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[合成生物学|合成生物学]]是一个新兴的学科，它使基因工程进一步将人工合成的材料从原材料引入生物体。

如果将来自另一物种的遗传物质添加到某生物体中，则所得生物称为遗传修饰生物。如果使用来自相同物种的遗传物质或可以与宿主自然[[繁殖|繁殖]]的物种，则称为[[同源基因|同源基因]]改造<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1007/s11540-008-9097-y |title=Cisgenesis, a New Tool for Traditional Plant Breeding, Should be Exempted from the Regulation on Genetically Modified Organisms in a Step by Step Approach |year=2008 |last1=Jacobsen |first1=E. |last2=Schouten |first2=H. J. |journal=Potato Research |volume=51 |pages=75–88}}</ref>遗传工程也可以用于从目标生物体去除遗传物质，创建一个基因敲除生物体<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1038/nm1001-1086 |year=2001 |last1=Capecchi |first1=Mario R. |journal=Nature Medicine |volume=7 |issue=10 |pages=1086–90 |pmid=11590420 |title=Generating mice with targeted mutations}}</ref>在欧洲，遗传修饰是遗传工程的同义词，而在[[美国|美国]]，“基因修饰”一词也可以指常规的育种方法。<ref>Staff [http://www.usda.gov/wps/portal/usda/usdahome?contentid=BiotechnologyGlosary.xml&navid= Biotechnology - Glossary of Agricultural Biotechnology Terms] {{Wayback|url=http://www.usda.gov/wps/portal/usda/usdahome?contentid=BiotechnologyGlosary.xml&navid= |date=20140830102928 }} United States Department of Agriculture, "Genetic modification: The production of heritable improvements in plants or animals for specific uses, via either genetic engineering or other more traditional methods. Some countries other than the United States use this term to refer specifically to genetic engineering.", Retrieved 5 November 2012</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Genetically Engineered Foods|first=James H.|last=Maryanski|publisher=Center for Food Safety and Applied Nutrition at the [[美国食品药品监督管理局|美国食品药品监督管理局]]|date=1999-10-19|url=http://www.fda.gov/NewsEvents/Testimony/ucm115032.htm|accessdate=2017-02-08|archive-date=2011-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110222202827/http://www.fda.gov/NewsEvents/Testimony/ucm115032.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[加拿大|加拿大]]的监管制度是基于产品是否具有新颖的特征，而不管来源的方法。换句话说，如果产品携带一些先前在物种中未发现的[[性狀|性状]]，则其被调节为遗传修饰，无论其是使用传统育种方法（例如选择育种，细胞融合，突变育种）还是遗传工程产生的。<ref>Evans, Brent and Lupescu, Mihai (15 July 2012) [http://gain.fas.usda.gov/Recent%20GAIN%20Publications/Agricultural%20Biotechnology%20Annual_Ottawa_Canada_07-20-2012.pdf Canada - Agricultural Biotechnology Annual – 2012] {{Wayback|url=http://gain.fas.usda.gov/Recent%20GAIN%20Publications/Agricultural%20Biotechnology%20Annual_Ottawa_Canada_07-20-2012.pdf |date=20131215160309 }} GAIN (Global Agricultural Information Network) report CA12029, United States Department of Agriculture, Foreifn Agricultural Service, Retrieved 5 November 2012</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=McHugen |first=Alan |title= Pandora's Picnic Basket |publisher=Oxford University Press |date=2000-09-14 |chapter=Chapter 1: Hors-d'oeuvres and entrees/What is genetic modification?  What are GMOs? |isbn=978-0198506744}}</ref><ref>Staff (28 November 2005) [http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/sr-sr/pubs/biotech/reg_gen_mod-eng.php Health Canada - The Regulation of Genetically Modified Food] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/sr-sr/pubs/biotech/reg_gen_mod-eng.php |date=20170610170104 }} Glossary definition of Genetically Modified: "An organism, such as a plant, animal or bacterium, is considered genetically modified if its genetic material has been altered through any method, including conventional breeding. A 'GMO' is a genetically modified organism.", Retrieved 5 November 2012</ref>在科学界，“基因工程”这个术语并不常用。取而代之的是更为具体的术语，例如“遗传修饰”或“转基因”。

== 歷史 ==
{{main article|基因工程历史}}

数千年来，人类通过选择性育种或人工选择。<ref name=Root>{{cite book|title=Domestication|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=WGDYHvOHwmwC}}|first=Clive |last=Root|year=2007|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Groups}}</ref>{{rp|1}}<ref name=Zohary>{{cite book |title=Domestication of Plants in the Old World: The origin and spread of plants in the old world|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=tc6vr0qzk_4C}}|first1=Daniel |last1=Zohary |first2=Maria |last2=Hopf |first3=Ehud |last3=Weiss|year=2012|publisher=Oxford University Press}}</ref>近年来，逐渐通过诱变改变了物种的基因组。而遗传工程作为直接操纵DNA、由人外部育种和突变是自20世纪70年代产生的。

“遗传工程”这个术语最早由[[杰克·威廉姆森|杰克·威廉姆森]]在1951年——也就是DNA在在遗传中的作用得到了[[阿弗雷德·赫希|阿弗雷德·赫希]]和[[玛莎·蔡斯|玛莎·蔡斯]]的证实的前一年——出版的科幻小说“龙之岛<ref>{{cite book|last=Stableford|first=Brian M.|first-link=|title=Historical dictionary of science fiction literature|page=133|year=2004|isbn=9780810849389|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=nzmIPZg5xicC|page=9}}}}</ref>中创作。1953年，[[詹姆斯·沃森|詹姆斯·沃森]]和[[弗朗西斯·克里克|弗朗西斯·克里克]]发现DNA分子具有[[双螺旋结构|双螺旋结构]]。[[斯丹利·温鲍姆|斯丹利·温鲍姆]]的1936年的科幻故事普罗透斯岛（Proteus Island）中探索了直接遗传操作的一般概念。

1972年，[[保罗·伯格|保罗·伯格]]通过将来自猴病毒SV40的DNA与[[λ病毒|λ病毒]]的DNA结合而产生了第一个重组DNA分子。<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1073/pnas.69.10.2904|last1=Jackson|title=Biochemical Method for Inserting New Genetic Information into DNA of Simian Virus 40: Circular SV40 DNA Molecules Containing Lambda Phage Genes and the Galactose Operon of Escherichia coli|first1=DA|last2=Symons|first2=RH|last3=Berg|first3=P|first8= David A. Jackson Robert H. Symons and Paul Berg|journal=PNAS|date=1972-10-01|volume=69|issue=10|pages=2904–2909|pmid=4342968|pmc=389671|bibcode = 1972PNAS...69.2904J }}</ref>在1973年，[[赫伯特·博耶|赫伯特·博耶]]和[[斯坦利·科恩|斯坦利·科恩]]通过将[[抗生素|抗生素]]抗性基因插入到[[大肠杆菌|大肠杆菌]]细菌的质粒中而产生了第一个遗传修饰生物。<ref>{{cite web|title=History of Genetics: Genetic Engineering Timeline|last=Arnold|first=Paul|year=2009|url=http://www.brighthub.com/science/genetics/articles/21983.aspx|accessdate=2017-02-08|archive-date=2019-05-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524051241/https://www.brighthub.com/science/genetics/articles/21983.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first1=Stanley N. |last1=Cohen |first2=Annie C. Y. |last2=Chang |url=http://www.pnas.org/content/70/5/1293.short |title=Recircularization and Autonomous Replication of a Sheared R-Factor DNA Segment in Escherichia coli Transformants — PNAS |publisher=Pnas.org |date=1973-05-01 |accessdate=2010-07-17 |archive-date=2019-05-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190521010134/https://www.pnas.org/content/70/5/1293.short |dead-url=no }}</ref>一年后，[[鲁道夫·耶尼施|鲁道夫·耶尼施]]通过将外来DNA引入其胚胎中创建了一种遗传修饰小鼠，使其成为世界上第一个遗传修饰动物<ref>Jaenisch, R. and Mintz, B. (1974 ) Simian virus 40 DNA sequences in DNA of healthy adult mice derived from preimplantation blastocysts injected with viral DNA. Proc. Natl. Acad. 71(4) 1250–1254 [http://www.pnas.org/content/71/4/1250] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pnas.org/content/71/4/1250 |date=20190707123834 }}</ref>这些成就导致了科学界对基因工程的潜在风险的关注，这些问题首先在1975年的[[阿西洛马会议|阿西洛马会议]]上进行了深入讨论。这次会议的主要建议之一是，在技术的安全性得到确认之前政府应加强对重组DNA研究的监督。<ref>{{cite journal | author = Berg P | year = 1975 | title = Summary statement of the Asilomar Conference on recombinant DNA molecules | url = http://www.pnas.org/content/72/6/1981.full.pdf | format = PDF | journal = Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A | volume = 72 | issue = 6 | pages = 1981–4 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.72.6.1981 | pmid = 806076 | last2 = Baltimore | first2 = D | last3 = Brenner | first3 = S | last4 = Roblin | first4 = RO | last5 = Singer | first5 = MF | pmc = 432675 | bibcode = 1975PNAS...72.1981B | display-authors = etal | access-date = 2017-02-08 | archive-date = 2011-07-15 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110715113724/http://www.pnas.org/content/72/6/1981.full.pdf }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://oba.od.nih.gov/rdna/nih_guidelines_oba.html |title=NIH Guidelines for research involving recombinant DNA molecules |access-date=2017-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120910070047/http://oba.od.nih.gov/rdna/nih_guidelines_oba.html |archive-date=2012-09-10 |dead-url=yes }}{{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120910070047/http://oba.od.nih.gov/rdna/nih_guidelines_oba.html |date=2012-09-10 }}</ref>
1976年，[[赫伯特·博耶|赫伯特·博耶]]和羅伯特·史旺森创立了遗传工程公司[[基因泰克|基因泰克]]（Genentech），该公司在大肠杆菌中生产了人类蛋白[[生长抑素|生长抑素]]。 基因泰克在1978年宣布生产遗传修饰生产的人[[胰岛素|胰岛素]]。<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1073/pnas.76.1.106 |last=Goeddel |first=David |first2=Dennis G. |last2=Kleid |first3=Francisco |last3=Bolivar |first4=Herbert L. |last4=Heyneker |first5=Daniel G. |last5=Yansura |first6=Roberto |last6=Crea |first7=Tadaaki |last7=Hirose |first8=Adam |last8=Kraszewski |first9=Keiichi |last9=Itakura |first10=Arthur D. |last10=Riggs |title=Expression in Escherichia coli of chemically synthesized genes for human insulin |journal=PNAS |date=January 1979 |volume=76 |issue=1 |pages=106–110 |url=http://www.pnas.org/content/76/1/106.full.pdf |pmid=85300 |pmc=382885 |bibcode=1979PNAS...76..106G |access-date=2017-02-08 |archive-date=2017-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115230742/http://www.pnas.org/content/76/1/106.full.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>1980年，美国最高法院在Diamond诉Chakrabarty案中裁定，遗传改变的生命可以获得专利。<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://supreme.justia.com/us/447/303/case.html |title=Diamond V Chakrabarty |volume=447 |author=US Supreme Court Cases from Justia & Oyez |publisher=Supreme.justia.com |date=1980-06-16 |accessdate=2010-07-17 |issue=303 |archive-date=2012-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107012535/http://supreme.justia.com/us/447/303/case.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>此種藉由细菌生產的胰岛素以「[[優泌林|優泌林]]」作為品牌名稱，在1982年經[[美国食品药物监督管理局|美国食品药物监督管理局]]批准销售。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,949646-1,00.html |title=Artificial Genes |work=TIME |date=1982-11-15 |accessdate=2010-07-17 |archive-date=2013-05-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130521070027/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,949646-1,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

