在材料科学中，基因修饰的病毒已经在学术实验室中用作组装更环保的锂离子电池的支架。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2009/virus-battery-0402.html |title=New virus-built battery could power cars, electronic devices |publisher=Web.mit.edu |date=2009-04-02 |accessdate=2010-07-17 |archive-date=2014-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301024048/http://web.mit.edu/newsoffice/2009/virus-battery-0402.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=102647672 |title=Hidden Ingredient In New, Greener Battery: A Virus |publisher=Npr.org |accessdate=2010-07-17 |archive-date=2019-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524081905/https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=102647672 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

