{{main article|基因改造食物}}
基因工程最有名和有争议的应用之一是创造和使用遗传修饰作物或遗传修饰生物，如[[萤光鱼|萤光鱼]]，用于生产遗传修饰食品和具有多种用途的材料。

遗传修饰食品作物的生产有四个主要目标<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/j.1753-4887.2008.00130.x|last=Magaña-Gómez |first=JA |last2=de la Barca |first2=A.M.|year=2009|title=Risk assessment of genetically modified crops for nutrition and health|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_nutrition-reviews_2009-01_67_1/page/n4|journal=Nutr. Rev.|volume=67|issue=1|pages=1–16|pmid=19146501}}</ref>，即：耐病虫害、提高作物价值、制造副产品和加快生长强化植株。

===环境保护===
遗传工程在保护和自然区域管理中具有潜在的应用。例如，已经提出通过病毒载体的基因转移作为控制入侵物种以及接种来自疾病的受威胁动物群的手段。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Angulo|first=E.|last2=Cooke|first2=B.|date=2002|title=First synthesize new viruses then regulate their release? The case of the wild rabbit|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_molecular-ecology_2002-12_11_12/page/2703|journal=Molecular Ecology|doi=10.1046/j.1365-294X.2002.01635.x|pmid=12453252|volume=11|pages=2703–9}}</ref>还提出了遗传修饰树作为赋予野生种群[[群体免疫|群体免疫]]的方法。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Adams|displayauthors=etal|date=2002-08-02|title=The Case for Genetic Engineering of Native and Landscape Trees against Introduced Pests and Diseases|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1523-1739.2002.00523.x/full|journal=Conservation Biology|doi=10.1046/j.1523-1739.2002.00523.x|pmid=|access-date=2016-05-16|volume=16|pages=874–879|archive-date=2017-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111041542/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1046/j.1523-1739.2002.00523.x/full}}</ref>随着气候变化和其他扰动导致生物体适应不良的风险增加，通过基因调整促进适应可能是减少灭绝风险的一个解决方案。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Thomas|displayauthors=etal|date=2013-09-25|title=Ecology: Gene tweaking for conservation|url=http://www.nature.com/news/ecology-gene-tweaking-for-conservation-1.13790|journal=Nature|doi=10.1038/501485a|pmid=24073449|access-date=2016-05-16|volume=501|pages=485–6|archive-date=2021-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210429091515/https://www.nature.com/news/ecology-gene-tweaking-for-conservation-1.13790}}</ref>遗传工程在保护中的应用迄今为止大部分是理论上的，还没有付诸实践。将需要进一步的实验来衡量这种做法的好处和成本。

==技术限制==

遗传工程的管理调控涉及政府为评估和管理与遗传修饰作物的开发和销售相关的风险而采取的措施。不同国家和地区针对遗传修饰作物的管理存在差异，其中美国和欧洲之间的差异最明显。根据基因工程产品的预期用途，在各国家的法规有所不同。例如，非食品用途的作物通常不由负责食品安全的机构审查。从20世纪80年代后期开始，评估包括[[联合国粮食及农业组织|粮农组织]]和[[世界卫生组织|世卫组织]]在内的组织在遗传修饰植物和食品安全方面的指导。<ref>WHO (1987): [http://www.inchem.org/documents/ehc/ehc/ehc70.htm Principles for the Safety Assessment of Food Additives and Contaminants in Food, Environmental Health Criteria 70] {{Wayback|url=http://www.inchem.org/documents/ehc/ehc/ehc70.htm |date=20191108080045 }}. World Health Organization, Geneva</ref><ref>WHO (1991): Strategies for assessing the safety of foods produced by biotechnology, Report of a Joint FAO/WHO Consultation. World Health Organization, Geneva ISBN 9789241561457. PDF download library.health.go.ug/download/file/fid/790 here]</ref><ref>WHO (1993): [http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/61636/1/WHO_FNU_FOS_93.6.pdf Health aspects of marker genes in genetically modified plants, Report of a WHO Workshop] {{Wayback|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/61636/1/WHO_FNU_FOS_93.6.pdf |date=20160101020636 }}. World Health Organization, Geneva</ref><ref>WHO (1995): [http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/58909/1/WHO_FNU_FOS_95.1.pdf Application of the principle of substantial equivalence to the safety evaluation of foods or food components from plants derived by modern biotechnology, Report of a WHO Workshop] {{Wayback|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/58909/1/WHO_FNU_FOS_95.1.pdf |date=20160101020636 }}. World Health Organization, Geneva</ref>

==争议==

批评者反对使用基因工程本身有几个理由，包括伦理问题<ref>{{cite web | last = Wendell | first = David | name-list-format = vanc | date = 2009-01-30 | url = http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/clinical-research/ | title = The Ethics of Clinical Research | work = The Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy (Fall 2012 Edition) | editor-first = Edward N. | editor-last = Zalta | access-date = 2017-02-10 | archive-date = 2022-04-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220414070014/https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/clinical-research/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | first = Corinne | last = Segal | name-list-format = vanc | work = Tufts Daily | date = 2012-09-17 | url = http://tuftsdaily.com/archives/2012/09/17/alleged-ethics-violations-surface-in-tufts-backed-study/ | title = Alleged ethics violations surface in Tufts-backed study | access-date = 2017-02-10 | archive-date = 2022-04-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220414070018/https://tuftsdaily.com/archives/2012/09/17/alleged-ethics-violations-surface-in-tufts-backed-study/ }}</ref>，生态问题<ref name="Piñeyro-Nelson_2009">{{cite journal | vauthors = Piñeyro-Nelson A, Van Heerwaarden J, Perales HR, Serratos-Hernández JA, Rangel A, Hufford MB, Gepts P, Garay-Arroyo A, Rivera-Bustamante R, Alvarez-Buylla ER | title = Transgenes in Mexican maize: molecular evidence and methodological considerations for GMO detection in landrace populations | journal = Molecular Ecology | volume = 18 | issue = 4 | pages = 750–61 | date = February 2009 | pmid = 19143938 | pmc = 3001031 | doi = 10.1111/j.1365-294X.2008.03993.x }}</ref>，与传统及有机农业的商业利益冲突，以及由于遗传修饰技术和遗传修饰生物体受知识产权法律的限制所引起的经济关注。遗传修饰生物也参与关于遗传修饰食品的争议，涉及遗传修饰作物生产的食品是否安全<ref name=Marden>{{cite web | first = Emily | last = Marden | name-list-format = vanc | url = http://lawdigitalcommons.bc.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2236&context=bclr | title = Risk and Regulation: U.S. Regulatory Policy on Genetically Modified Food and Agriculture | work = 44 B.C.L. Rev. 733 | date = 2003 | quote = By the late 1990s, public awareness of GM foods reached a critical level and a number of public interest groups emerged to focus on the issue.  One of the early groups to focus on the issue was Mothers for Natural Law ("MFNL"), an Iowa-based organization that aimed to ban GM foods from the market....The Union of Concerned Scientists ("UCS"), an alliance of 50,000 citizens and scientists, has been another prominent voice on the issue.... As the pace of GM products entering the market increased in the 1990s, UCS became a vocal critic of what it saw as the agency's collusion with industry and failure to fully take account of allergenicity and other safety issues. | accessdate = 2017-02-10 | archive-date = 2019-11-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191108111929/http://lawdigitalcommons.bc.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2236&context=bclr | dead-url = no }}</ref>
，是否应该贴标签，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foodstandards.gov.au/scienceandeducation/publications/consumerattitiudes |title=Consumer Attitudes Survey 2007, A benchmark survey of consumers' attitudes to food issues |publisher=Food Standards Australia New Zealand |date=January 2008 |access-date=2012-11-05 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110217031329/http://www.foodstandards.gov.au/scienceandeducation/publications/consumerattitiudes/ |archivedate=2011-02-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>以及是否需要遗传修饰作物来满足世界粮食需求。<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/sowing-a-gene-revolution/|title = Sowing a Gene Revolution|last = Raney|first = Terri|date = September 2007|work = Scientific American|access-date = 2014-10-26|last2 = Pingali|first2 = Prabhu|name-list-format = vanc|archive-date = 2022-03-10|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220310052812/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/sowing-a-gene-revolution/}}</ref><ref name=Lal>{{cite book|editor1-first= Rattan |editor1-last= Lal |editor2-first= Peter R |editor2-last= Hobbs |editor3-first= Norman |editor3-last= Uphoff |editor4-first= David O | editor4-last = Hansen | name-list-format = vanc |title= Sustainable Agriculture and the International Rice-Wheat System |url= {{google books|plainurl=y|id=l9luzqkqj_UC |page=12}} |access-date= 2013-05-12 |year= 2004 |publisher= {{tsl|en|CRC Press||CRC Press}} |location= |isbn= 9780824754914|ref= harv  }}</ref>{{rp|12}} <ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Kiers ET, Leakey RR, Izac AM, Heinemann JA, Rosenthal E, Nathan D, Jiggins J | title = Ecology. Agriculture at a crossroads | journal = Science | volume = 320 | issue = 5874 | pages = 320–1 | date = April 2008 | pmid = 18420917 | doi = 10.1126/science.1158390 }}</ref><ref name=IAASTD>{{cite web|title=Agriculture at a Crossroads (c) 2009"|url=http://www.unep.org/dewa/agassessment/reports/IAASTD/EN/Agriculture%20at%20a%20Crossroads_Synthesis%20Report%20(English).pdf|publisher=International Assessment of Agricul